###  http:/purl.org/scimin-crm-mwf/LeachingOperation
<http:/purl.org/scimin-crm-mwf/LeachingOperation> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                  rdfs:subClassOf <http:/purl.org/scimin-crm-mwf/MineralProcessingOperation> ;
                                                  rdfs:comment "MWEI BREF : Extraction of soluble components from raw materials by the action of a percolating liquid (e.g. water). For example, gold can be extracted by heap leaching of a porous ore, or pulverised extractive waste from mineral processing. Other methods are tank leaching of ore, concentrates or extractive waste from mineral processing and in-situ leaching. Leaching may also be an unwanted process leading to polluted drainage (see \"leachate\"). Bio-leaching is a particular form of leaching involving living organisms"@en .


